ously thought, Pivotal Politics remakes our understanding of American lawmaking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aLegislationzUnited States. 0aSeparation of powerszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aKrehbiel, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226452739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226452739.jpg  a978-3-11-066785-1  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aGBV-deGruyter-alles